# No assign module variable

> Prevent assignment to the `module` variable.

title: No assign module variable
content:
## [Why This Error Occurred](#why-this-error-occurred)

A value is being assigned to the `module` variable. The `module` variable is already used and it is highly likely that assigning to this variable will cause errors.
preview: A value is being assigned to the `module` variable. The `module` variable is already used and it is highly likely that assigning to this variable will cause errors.

title: No assign module variable
content:
## [Possible Ways to Fix It](#possible-ways-to-fix-it)

Use a different variable name:

example.js

```
let myModule = {...}
```
